<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="chorology">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus morio" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus morio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Holarctic species with a trans-Palaearctic distribution. The first records for Iran (West and East Azarbaijan) were published only recently by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghahari, H" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="1959 - 1968" refId="B22" refString="Ghahari, H, Anlas, S, Sakenin, H, Ostovan, H, Tabari, M, 2009b. A contribution to the rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinoidea: Staphylinidae) of Iranian rice fields and surrounding grasslands. Linzer biologische Beitraege 41 (2): 1959 - 1968" title="A contribution to the rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinoidea: Staphylinidae) of Iranian rice fields and surrounding grasslands." volume="41" year="2009 b">Ghahari et al. (2009b</bibRefCitation>
: 1964). However, we were not given the opportunity to see the underlying specimens. Like other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus melanarius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus melanarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus morio" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus morio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be rare in Iran and restricted to the northwest of the country, because we collected it in the northern Zagros (Hamedan Province) only (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–18" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 13 - 18. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 13. Stenus guttula species group: ○ Stenus erythrocnemus, ● Stenus maculiger; 14. Stenus hopffgarteni species group: ○ Stenus fuscicornis; 15. Stenus humilis species group: ○ Stenus callidus; 16. Stenus impressus and Stenus incanus species groups: ○ Stenus heinzianus, △ Stenus taurus; 17. Stenus latifrons and Stenus melanarius species groups: ▲ Stenus latifrons, ○ Stenus incrassatus, □ Stenus morio, ● Stenus peripherus; 18. Stenus melanopus species group: ○ Stenus atratulus, ● Stenus piscator." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures13-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74430" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="biogeographical characterization">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Biogeographical characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
The trans-Palaearctic distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus morio" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Stenus morio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can not be explained by particular Pleistocene refuges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
